Libraries We Used

streamlit: Streamlit is an open-source Python framework used to create interactive web applications for data science and machine learning projects. It allows you to turn data scripts into shareable web apps 
quickly and with minimal coding effort. Hereâ€™s a basic overview of what you can do with Streamlit.
Key Features:
Interactive Widgets: Streamlit provides a variety of widgets (like sliders, buttons, and text inputs) that allow users to interact with the data and models in real-time.
Seamless Integration: You can integrate Streamlit with popular Python libraries like NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Plotly, and others to create interactive visualizations and data analyses.
Automatic Updates: Any change in the Python code or data automatically updates the app in real-time, without needing to refresh the page.
Deployment: Streamlit apps can be deployed to the web easily using platforms like Streamlit Cloud, Heroku, or AWS.




openai:The OpenAI Python library provides convenient access to OpenAI's GPT models, including GPT-4, which powers this chat. You can use the library to interact with these models for various applications
like text generation, question answering, summarization, and more.
Installation:
To use the OpenAI Python library, you first need to install it. You can do this using pip:
pip install openai

